                        <h3 class="expand-click w_icon_24 icon_general">WordPress plugins used by The Money Pit®</h3>
                        <div class="expand-content">
                          <p>
                            The Money Pit, like any other website built within the WordPress framework, uses some WordPress plugins (“<b>WP Plugin/s</b>”).<br/>A plugin is typically a software component (a code or a software itself) that adds specific features to an existing program, therefore allowing its customization.<br/>The plugins may be used for multiple purposes. In particular, there are:<br/><br/>- Social plugins: they enable and facilitate the communications between the website and the chosen social networks<br/>- Analytics plugins: they enable statistics to be extracted from the User's navigation behavior or from other data (e.g. heat mapping tools, keywords, locations, referrers, tweets, languages etc.)<br/>- SEO plugins: they help to make the website content more readily and easily available for any research performed through any search engine (Google, Yahoo etc.)<br/>- Feature - enabling plugins: they allow the website to receive Users' comments, allow and/or improve the researches, geolocate users, enable the popup windows to appear and so on.<br/><br/>The majority of WP Plugin is developed by third parties, while some others are developed in house by Automattic, Inc., the company that owns and runs WordPress. WP Plugins are tools meant to improve the functionality and performance of a website and increase its features, and therefore, they do not normally involve any Personal Data processing or sharing.<br/>However, as far as WP Plugins made by third parties are concerned, any of such third parties may have access to the User's Personal Data collected through the relevant WP Plugin, if the same has been coded with that purpose.<br/>Any Personal Data processing by the aforesaid third parties shall be carried out according to their privacy policies, over which the Owner cannot possibly exercise any type of control or influence. <br/>The Money Pit uses WP Plugins, both coded on its own and by third parties, that enable The Money Pit to run the following features: geolocation, connection to social network platforms, User registration and authentication, advertising and analytics.<br/>To receive the full list of the WP Plugins used by The Money Pit or for further information about them, User can contact the Owner at the contact details available in the present document.
                          </p>
